HEADWORD: Forejudger
<hw>Fore*judg"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eng. Law)</fld>
<def>A judgment by which one is deprived or put out of a right or thing
in question.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forejudgment</ent>⟦br⟧
